        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 11:12PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 1112 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles east of Brewster, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Taylor, Calamus Reservoir State Recreation Area, Fox Bayou, Almeria
Meadow State Wildlife Management Area, Virginia Smith Dam, Hannamon
Bayou Campground, Kent Diversion Dam State Wildlife Management Area,
Homestead Knolls Campground, Horseshoe Bend Lake, Almeria, Nunda
Shoal Campground, Deverre, and Valley View Flat Campground.

This includes Highway 183 between mile markers 123 and 145.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
north central Nebraska.</instruction>
